@startuml Storage Enforcement - Configuration Resolution Logic
!theme default
title Storage Enforcement System - Configuration Resolution Decision Tree

start
:Receive request with
organisation_id (optional);

if (organisation_id provided?) then (yes)
  :Query: find_by_organisation(
    organisation_id
  );

  if (Organisation config found?) then (yes)
    :✅ Use organisation-specific config;
    stop
  else (no)
    :Org config not found,
    continue to system default;
  endif
else (no)
  :No organisation_id provided,
  skip org lookup;
endif

:Query: find_system_default();

if (System default found?) then (yes)
  :✅ Use system default config;
  stop
else (no)
  :System default not found,
  use internal defaults;
endif

:✅ Use hardcoded internal defaults
(should rarely reach here);
stop

note right
  **Typical Scenarios:**

  **B2B (Organisation):**
  - organisation_id='school-123'
  - Lookup finds soft enforcement config
  - Use org-specific rules

  **B2C (Individual):**
  - organisation_id=null
  - Skip to system default
  - Use hard enforcement config

  **New Organisation:**
  - organisation_id='new-org'
  - No org config yet
  - Fallback to system default
  - Admin can create org-specific later

  **Failsafe:**
  - Internal defaults never fail
  - Ensures system always has config
  - Should never be needed in practice
end note

@enduml
